Primary_Text: Ich habe etwas <*irgend etwas> verloren. Rate mal, was!
Translated_Text: I lost something. Guess what!

Primary_Text: Ich habe etwas/irgend etwas verloren, aber ich weiss nicht, was.
Translated_Text: I lost something, but I don't know what.

Primary_Text: Sie möchte jemanden/irgend jemanden mit schwarzen Haaren heiraten.
Translated_Text: She wants to marry someone [non-specific/specific] with black hair.

Primary_Text: Hast du (irgend) etwas gehört?
Translated_Text: Did you hear anything?

Primary_Text: Ist sie irgend-wann/je in Chittagong gewesen?
Translated_Text: Has she ever been to Chittagong?

Primary_Text: Wenn (irgend) jemand anruft, sag mir Bescheid!
Translated_Text: If anyone calls, tell me!

Primary_Text: Ich glaube nicht, dass hier je/irgend-wann (irgend) jemand war.
Translated_Text: I don't think that anyone has ever been here.

Primary_Text: Joan Baez sang besser als irgend jemand je zuvor.
Translated_Text: Joan Baez sang better than anyone ever before.

Primary_Text: Dieses Problem kann irgend jemand lösen.
Translated_Text: This problem can be solved by anyone.

Primary_Text: Dieses Problem kann jeder lösen.
Translated_Text: This problem can be solved by anyone.

Primary_Text: Joan Baez singt besser als jede andere Sängerin.
Translated_Text: Joan Baez sings better than any other singer.

Primary_Text: ohne jede/irgend-welche Hilfe
Translated_Text: without any help

Primary_Text: Sie stritt jede/irgend-eine Beteilingung ab.
Translated_Text: She denied any participation.

Primary_Text: Niemand ist gekommen.
Translated_Text: Nobody has come.

Primary_Text: Ich habe niemandem (irgend) etwas gesagt.
Translated_Text: I didn't tell anything to anybody.

Primary_Text: Er heeft vanmorgen iemand opgebeld. (Raad eens wie./ Ik weet niet meer wie het was.)
Translated_Text: Someone phoned this morning. (Guess who./ I don't remember who it was.)

Primary_Text: Koop iets/wat dan ook voor haar verjaardag.
Translated_Text: Buy something for her birthday.

Primary_Text: Zou er nog iemand/wie dan ook komen?
Translated_Text: Will anyone else come?

Primary_Text: Als je iets/wat dan ook ziet, waarschuw me dan.
Translated_Text: If you see anything, tell me.

Primary_Text: zonder iemand/wie dan ook
Translated_Text: without anybody

Primary_Text: Het is moeilijk om iets/wat dan ook te zien.
Translated_Text: It is difficult to see anything.

Primary_Text: De jongen loopt harder dan wie dan ook in zijn klass.
Translated_Text: The boy runs faster than anyone in his class.

Primary_Text: Je mag wie dan ook uitnodigen.
Translated_Text: You may invite anyone.

Primary_Text: Niemand heeft opgebeld.
Translated_Text: Nobody called.

Primary_Text: Het is nu kouder dan in enige vorige winter.
Translated_Text: It is now colder than in any previous winter.

Primary_Text: zonder enige help
Translated_Text: without any help

Primary_Text: Heeft hij enig succes gehad met al zijn pogingen?
Translated_Text: Has he had any success with all his attempts?

Primary_Text: Als hij enig succes heeft, dan komt dat door zijn goede kontakten.
Translated_Text: If he has any success, that is due to his good connections.

Primary_Text: Quelqu'un m'attend. C'est lui que j'épouserai.
Translated_Text: Someone is waiting for me. It's him that I will marry.

Primary_Text: Quelqu'un est à la porte. Je ne sais pas qui.
Translated_Text: Somebody is at the door. I don't know who.

Primary_Text: Elle veut épouser quelqu'un aux cheveux noirs.
Translated_Text: She wants to marry someone with black hair.

Primary_Text: As-tu écouté quelque chose?
Translated_Text: Have you heard anything?

Primary_Text: Si l'art n'était vraiment qu'un prolongement de la vie, valait-il de lui rien sacrifier?
Translated_Text: If art were really only a continuation of life, would it be worth sacrificing anything for it?

Primary_Text: Comment peut-on en conclure quoi que ce soit sur l'ordre de la pensée?
Translated_Text: How can one conclude anything from it about the order of thoughts?

Primary_Text: Je vous rends responsable si rien/quelque chose s'ébruite dans la presse.
Translated_Text: I hold you responsible if anything transpires in the media.

Primary_Text: Éveillez-moi s'il arrive quoi que ce soit.
Translated_Text: Wake me up if anything happens.

Primary_Text: Je ne vois rien.
Translated_Text: I cannot see anything.

Primary_Text: Personne n' jamais dit rien.
Translated_Text: Nobody ever said anything.

Primary_Text: Je n'ai vu qui que ce soit.
Translated_Text: I haven't seen anybody.

Primary_Text: Je doute que personne y réussisse.
Translated_Text: I doubt that anybody will succeed in it.

Primary_Text: J'hésite à rien écrire sur cela/à écrire quoi que ce soit sur cela.
Translated_Text: I hesitate to write anything about that.

Primary_Text: Il parle mieux qu'aucun orateur.
Translated_Text: He speaks better than any orator.

Primary_Text: Je préfère de beaucoup fermer les yeux que lui reprocher quoi que ce soit qui puisse vous ennuyer.
Translated_Text: I much prefer to close my eyes than to blame him for anything that could annoy you.

Primary_Text: Vous pouvez dire quoi que ce soit.
Translated_Text: You can say anything.

Primary_Text: Demandez à quiconque des assistents!
Translated_Text: Ask any of the assistants!

Primary_Text: Je le sais mieux que quiconque.
Translated_Text: I know it better than anyone.

Primary_Text: Il n'est pas permis de parler de ceci à quiconque.
Translated_Text: It isn't possible to talk about this to anyobody.

Primary_Text: Si quiconque insiste pour me parler, dites qu'on m'écrive.
Translated_Text: If anyone insists on talking to me, tell them to write to me.

Primary_Text: Tu peux dire n'importe quoi.
Translated_Text: You can say anything.

Primary_Text: Le général avait compris assez tôt que cette guerre, plus que n'importe quelle guerre dans le passé, était une guerre de réserves d'hommes et de matériel.
Translated_Text: The general had understood pretty soon that this war, more than any war in the past, was a war of human and material resources.

Primary_Text: Qualcuno è venuto – indovina chi!

Primary_Text: Non trovo la penna, eppure in qualche parte l'avrò messa.
